# Git commits

## Author attribution

- Commits must be authored **only by the user**, not by Cursor or any agent.
- **Never** add `Co-authored-by`, `Signed-off-by`, or any other commit trailer attributing Cursor or an AI tool.
- Write commit messages as if the user is committing their own work.

## When committing

- Only commit when the user explicitly asks.
- Use a HEREDOC for the commit message body.
- Do not amend or force-push unless the user explicitly asks.
- If rewriting history to remove co-author trailers, use `--force-with-lease` only when the user has asked to fix history.

## Example

```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Short summary line.

Optional body in plain sentences.
EOF
)"
```

No trailers. No `Co-authored-by` line.
